review_blob: Light golden pour with a small head. Pine-orange citrus hoppy. Refreshingly thin, not heavy.
Wonderful mid-light golden pour. Taste is fantastically smooth and clean. Intentionally vague. It is a unique brew. Difficult to characterize. Excellent!
Luscious caramel colored pour with a nice head. A hearty Double IPA with a smooth texture. Not overly citrus, but just enough.
beer_name: Singlecut Billy Full Stack Double IPA

review_blob: Golden caramel pour with a modest head. Full of flavor. Citrus and hoppy. I lke it.
Hazy orange pour with a thin head. Notes of citrus. Not sure that I can compare this to another. It is unique and good.
beer_name: Midnight Sun Fallen Angel Golden Strong Ale

review_blob: Very nice golden pour with a thin head. Not overwhelmingly hopped. Some citrus. Refreshing.
beer_name: Anchorage / Hill Farmstead Distant Matter IPA

review_blob: Beautiful amber pour with a nice head. Malty and caramelly, but not too much so. The high alchohol is not noticeable.
beer_name: Dark Horse Double Crooked Tree IPA

review_blob: Beautiful dark pour with an ample head. A dark beer lover should give this a try. You will enjoy the full bodied taste.
Dark pour with a creamy head. Good lacing. Extremely gratifying beer. Coffee, vanilla and more.
Very nice hoppiness with some spicey aftertaste. the aferrtaste is definitely lingeringgggg.
Wonderful dark pour a moderate head. As advertised, coffee and chocolate at the start then toasty after that.
What beautiful dark pour and creamy head. Spicey and fruity at the same time. The flavors remain on my palate long after swallowing. Perhaps the perfect dark beer.
Beautiful dark pour with an ample long lasting head. Very tasty bourbon and oats. One of the best stouts ive had.
beer_name: Boulder Beer Obovoid Oak-Aged Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: Nice golden pour with small head. Light spice with orange on the back end. Overall, a refreshing drink.
Dark pour with ample head. Heavy spice that is long and strong in my throat. A sipper for sure.
Copper-gold pour with decent head and nice lacing. Mild pine-fruity hops. A  somewhat hearty DIPA.

beer_brewer_name: Pretty Things Beer and Ale Project
review_blob: Golden-orange pour with a modest head. Tangy hops. Pineapple aftertaste. Quite refreshing.
Dark brown pour. Earthy (?) malt taste. At first, seemed like a rough concoction, but I later came to appreciate that was the intention. It is actually mildly complex and pleasant.
Very nice dark yellow (?) pour with thick head and excellent lacing. Abundant hops with citrus-pine.
beer_name: Laughing Dog Devil Dog Imperial IPA

review_blob: Blind Tiger event. Very dark pour with creamy head. More subtle in flavor than some other ASAs.
beer_name: Mad River Rorschach Two (Double Brown Ale)

review_blob: Hazy yellow pour with a modest head. Mild spice with a twist of orange citrus. Quite a nice refreshing summer drink.
Golden yellow pour with thin bubbly head. Semi sweet hoppiness. Mild lemon citrus. Light, not heavy.
beer_name: Kuhnhenn Double Rice India Pale Ale (DRIPA)

review_blob: Beautiful dark pour with creamy head. Maltier than other Black IPAs. The citrus hops make it quite refreshing.. Dark beer lovers have a warm weather  option.
beer_name: Firestone Walker Wookey Jack Black Rye IPA

review_blob: My highest score ever. Copper pour with nice head. Very nice balance of malts and hops. A must try for the serious...
Golden pour with modest head. Modest piney hops. Like many IPAs... Many good ones.
Hazy yellow with modest head and lacing. Light wheat and hops. Very pleasant to drink... Refreshing.
Golden yellow pour. Tangy hop-citrus. Right up there with some of the best DIPAs I have had.
Golden orange pour with small head. Mild pine-citrus with hoppy notes. Pretty refreshing... Give it a try.
From a can. Taste of mildly piney hops. Similar to a DIPA, but has its own distinction. Quite nice!
Dark brown pour with medium head. Fruity taste. Mild hops. Mild roasted malts. Interesting Americsn Strong.
Beautiful dark amber pour with small head. The high alchohol is hidden behind the deep citrus and mild oak. Very nice.
Murky gold pour, looks like apple cider. The blend of a traditional IPA with a wheat beer makes a good combo.
Brought out of retirement..  I guess it is an okay brew, not really a Belgian IPA specialist. Very sweet.. beware.
beer_name: Smuttynose Short Batch #2 Brett and I

review_blob: Deep amber pour with average head. Some lacing. Maltier than other standard IPAs, apparently that is the English heritage. Pretty good offbest standard IPA.
Orange pour with very small head. Very mild spicing and citrus. Not a regular Saison drinker, so its hard to compare.
beer_name: Smuttynose Big Beer Series: Farmhouse Ale

review_blob: Copper orange pour with excellent lacing. Definitely among the best DIPAs I have had. Creamier than others.
Nice copper pour with good head and lacing. Prevalant wood taste makes it a nice diversion from standard DIPAs.
beer_name: Great Divide Anniversary Wood Aged Double IPA

review_blob: Caramel-orange pour with a thin head and nice lacing. Hops galore. Pine-orange citrus. Quite refreshing.
Nice murky golden pour with high carbonation head. Moderate but notable hops with mild orange-citrus aftertaste. Not bad.
Herbilicious. All of my favorite pizza toppings in a beer. Parsley, sage, rosemary and thyme.
beer_name: Dogfish Head / Victory / Stone Saison du BUFF

review_blob: 16 oz pour of golden goodness. Heavy hops, pineapple and grapefruit abound. Pungent something.. very good.
Dark brown pour with ample beige head and good lacing. Malty chocolate milk with a kick... Good.
Murky orange pour with thin head. Wheaty pineapple-orange with mild hops. Somewhat heavy taste.... nice
Dark pour with thinnish head. Moderate hops with roasted malts. Similar to Black IPA.
Poured into a glass from a bottle. Dark brown with small head. As advertised,  more of a brown IPA than a black one. Good hops and pine.
beer_name: Stone / The Alchemist / Ninkasi More Brown than Black IPA

review_blob: Unique sour (in a good way) taste. Deep copper red with a thin head. Nice hops. Definitely a sipper.
Hazy golden hue with nearly non-existent head. Piney hops. Refreshing. Not full bodied.
Murky brown with a thin head. Similar to other Olds Ive had. Mild malts. Some fruits: apricot, plum, ..? Not bad. Brooklyn Brewery event at the Tiger.
Amber-red pour with nice head and lacing. Mild citrus (grapefuit?) with ample hops. Darker than most IPAs. Very nice.
Very nice Quad. Dark copper with thin head. Excellent mix of the usual quad flavors: dried fruit, plum, lightly roasted malt,..  I will probably have another before the tap runs dry.
